---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import highlights from "../data/highlights.json";
import agenda from "../data/agenda.json";
import speakers from "../data/speakers.json";
import sponsors from "../data/sponsors.json";
import attendees from "../data/attendees.json";
import site from "../data/site.json";

const ticketUrl = "https://shop.osaango.com/category/apiops-helsinki-2026";
const partnerUrl = "https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1bXmS1AlfLN40FQ6Ws6ldm9BffD1sS_BW/edit?usp=sharing&ouid=108887358045542967446&rtpof=true&sd=true";
const speakerUrl = "https://tally.so/r/LZW5kO";
---

<BaseLayout title="APIOps Helsinki Conference 2026">
  <nav>
    <div class="container nav-inner">
      <div>
        <strong>APIOps Helsinki</strong>
      </div>
      <button
        class="nav-toggle"
        type="button"
        aria-label="Toggle navigation menu"
        aria-expanded="false"
        aria-controls="top-navigation"
      >
        <span></span>
        <span></span>
        <span></span>
      </button>
      <div class="nav-links" id="top-navigation">
        <a href="#agenda">Agenda</a>
        <a href="#tracks">Tracks</a>
        <a href="#community">Community</a>
        <a href="#partners">Partners</a>
        <a href={ticketUrl}>Tickets</a>
        <a class="button primary" href={ticketUrl}>Register Now</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

    <script>
    const navToggle = document.querySelector(".nav-toggle");
    const navLinks = document.querySelector(".nav-links");

    navToggle?.addEventListener("click", () => {
      navLinks?.classList.toggle("is-open");
      const isExpanded = navLinks?.classList.contains("is-open") || false;
      navToggle.setAttribute("aria-expanded", String(isExpanded));
    });

    window.addEventListener("resize", () => {
      if (window.innerWidth > 720 && navLinks?.classList.contains("is-open")) {
        navLinks.classList.remove("is-open");
        navToggle?.setAttribute("aria-expanded", "false");
      }
    });
  </script>

  <header class="hero" style={`--hero-image: url('${site.hero.backgroundImage}')`}>
    <div class="container hero-content">
      <span class="badge">June 2-3, 2026 · Epicenter Helsinki</span>
      <h1>APIOps Helsinki Conference 2026</h1>
      <p class="meta">Strategy · AI-Driven APIs · Community Co-Creation</p>
      <p>
        APIs are products, platforms, and the foundation for AI-driven systems.
      </p>
      <p>
        Join Finland’s premier API gathering for two days of focused strategy sessions,
        hands-on clinics, and peer-led community building. Designed for practitioners who want to advance their API and integration practices in a collaborative, hype-free environment.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="button primary" href={ticketUrl}>Buy Tickets</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href={partnerUrl}>Become a Partner</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

    <section class="section" id="about">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-title">
        <h2>What is APIOps?</h2>
        <p>A working conference for API and integration practitioners.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <p>
          APIOps Helsinki Conference is a practitioner-driven event for people who work with API ownership,
          governance, platform models, and AI-era integration decisions in real organisations.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is not a hype-driven API or AI event, and not a vendor expo. It is designed to help participants
          think more clearly, compare approaches with peers, and leave with concrete next steps.
        </p>
      </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section highlight-row" id="difference">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-title">
        <h2>Why isn't it called apidays Helsinki &amp; North like in previous years?</h2>
        <p>Essentials of the event is the same, but with a new name and focus on APIOps, due to the growing interest in the APIOps practices, and the open APIOps Cycles method. The global <b>apidays</b> organization is our partner, not main organizer. This is a controlled experiment, to try some new formats that can be more community-driven, and maintain local community engagement.</p>
                <p>Read more about APIOps in the blog <a href="https://www.osaango.com/blog/what-is-apiops/"><b><u>What is APIOps?</u></b></a> and <a href="https://www.osaango.com/blog/bridging-the-gap-where-does-product-management-fit-in-apiops-and-devops/"><b><u>Bridging the Gap: Where does product management fit in APIOps and DevOps?</u></b></a></p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid highlight-grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Community-driven formats</h3>
          <p>Clinics, workshops, and guided unconference sessions are part of the core program.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>The proven good stuff stays</h3>
          <p>Focused on the Finnish ecosystem, curated talks without sales pitches, and two parallel tracks.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Single shared experience</h3>
          <p>No fragmented expo hall. The goal is depth, practical insight, and concrete outcomes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


    <section class="section highlight-row" id="tracks">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="grid highlight-grid">
          {highlights.map((item) => (
            <div class="card">
              <span class="badge">APIOps Focus</span>
              <h3>{item.title}</h3>
              <p>{item.description}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

 <section class="section" id="agenda">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-title">
        <h2>Conference Agenda</h2>
        <p>June 2-3, 2026 · Epicenter Helsinki, Mikonkatu 9</p>
      </div>
      <div class="split" id="day">
        {agenda.map((day) => (
          <div class="card agenda-card">
            <div class={`agenda-header ${day.color}`}>
              {day.day}: {day.theme} · {day.date}
            </div>
            <div class="agenda-track-headings">
              <span class="track-heading">Time</span>
              <span class="track-heading">Track A</span>
              <span class="track-heading">Track B</span>
            </div>
            <ul class="agenda-list" id="day">
              {day.items.map((item) => (
                <li class={item.tracks ? "agenda-row has-tracks" : "agenda-row is-shared"}>
                  <span class="agenda-time">{item.time}</span>
                  {item.tracks ? (
                    <>
                      <div class="agenda-track-item">
                        <span class="agenda-track-label">Track A</span>
                        <span class="agenda-topic">{item.tracks.a.title}</span>
                        {item.tracks.a.speaker && (
                          <span class="agenda-speaker">{item.tracks.a.speaker}</span>
                        )}
                      </div>
                      <div class="agenda-track-item">
                        <span class="agenda-track-label">Track B</span>
                        <span class="agenda-topic">{item.tracks.b.title}</span>
                        {item.tracks.b.speaker && (
                          <span class="agenda-speaker">{item.tracks.b.speaker}</span>
                        )}
                      </div>
                    </>
                  ) : (
                    <div class="agenda-shared-item">
                      <span class="agenda-track-label">Shared session</span>
                      <span class="agenda-topic">{item.title}</span>
                      {item.speaker && <span class="agenda-speaker">{item.speaker}</span>}
                    </div>
                  )}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <div style="text-align:center; margin-top: 2rem;">
        <!-- <a class="button primary" href={ticketUrl}>See Full Agenda</a> -->
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <section class="section" id="community">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-title">
        <h2>Who Should Attend</h2>
        <p>Real insights and peer conversations, not expo noise.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid attend-grid" id="title">
        {attendees.map((audience) => (
          <div class="card">
            <h4>{audience.title}</h4>
            <p>{audience.description}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="speakers">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-title">
        <h2>Featured Speakers</h2>
        <p>Leaders from Finland’s API, platform, and AI ecosystems.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid speaker-grid" id="name">
        {speakers.map((speaker) => (
          <div class="card speaker-card">
            <div class="speaker-avatar">
              {speaker.avatar ? (
                <img src={speaker.avatar} alt={`Portrait of ${speaker.name}`} loading="lazy" />
              ) : (
                speaker.name
                  .split(" ")
                  .map((name) => name[0])
                  .join("")
              )}
            </div>
            <h3>{speaker.name}</h3>
            <p>
              {speaker.title} @{speaker.company}
            </p>
            {/* <p>{speaker.bio}</p> */}
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
        <div style="text-align:center; margin-top: 2rem;">
              <a class="button primary" href={speakerUrl}>Apply to speak</a>
        </div>
    </div>
  </section>

 <section class="section highlight-row" id="partners">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-title">
        <h2>Partners</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid sponsor-grid" id="name">
        {sponsors.gold.map((sponsor) => (
          <div class="card sponsor-card">
            {sponsor.url ? (
              <a class="sponsor-link" href={sponsor.url} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
                <div class="sponsor-media">
                  {sponsor.logo ? (
                    <img src={sponsor.logo} alt={`${sponsor.name} logo`} loading="lazy" />
                  ) : (
                    <span class="sponsor-name">{sponsor.name}</span>
                  )}
                </div>
                <p class="sponsor-name">{sponsor.name}</p>
                <p class="sponsor-tier">Gold</p>
              </a>
            ) : (
              <>
                <div class="sponsor-media">
                  {sponsor.logo ? (
                    <img src={sponsor.logo} alt={`${sponsor.name} logo`} loading="lazy" />
                  ) : (
                    <span class="sponsor-name">{sponsor.name}</span>
                  )}
                </div>
                <p class="sponsor-name">{sponsor.name}</p>
                <p class="sponsor-tier">Gold</p>
              </>
            )}
          </div>
        ))}
        {sponsors.silver.map((sponsor) => (
          <div class="card sponsor-card">
            {sponsor.url ? (
              <a class="sponsor-link" href={sponsor.url} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
                <div class="sponsor-media">
                  {sponsor.logo ? (
                    <img src={sponsor.logo} alt={`${sponsor.name} logo`} loading="lazy" />
                  ) : (
                    <span class="sponsor-name">{sponsor.name}</span>
                  )}
                </div>
                <p class="sponsor-name">{sponsor.name}</p>
                <p class="sponsor-tier">Silver</p>
              </a>
            ) : (
              <>
                <div class="sponsor-media">
                  {sponsor.logo ? (
                    <img src={sponsor.logo} alt={`${sponsor.name} logo`} loading="lazy" />
                  ) : (
                    <span class="sponsor-name">{sponsor.name}</span>
                  )}
                </div>
                <p class="sponsor-name">{sponsor.name}</p>
                <p class="sponsor-tier">Silver</p>
              </>
            )}
          </div>
        ))}
        {sponsors.community.map((sponsor) => (
          <div class="card sponsor-card">
            {sponsor.url ? (
              <a class="sponsor-link" href={sponsor.url} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
                <div class="sponsor-media">
                  {sponsor.logo ? (
                    <img src={sponsor.logo} alt={`${sponsor.name} logo`} loading="lazy" />
                  ) : (
                    <span class="sponsor-name">{sponsor.name}</span>
                  )}
                </div>
                <p class="sponsor-name">{sponsor.name}</p>
                <p class="sponsor-tier">Community</p>
              </a>
            ) : (
              <>
                <div class="sponsor-media">
                  {sponsor.logo ? (
                    <img src={sponsor.logo} alt={`${sponsor.name} logo`} loading="lazy" />
                  ) : (
                    <span class="sponsor-name">{sponsor.name}</span>
                  )}
                </div>
                <p class="sponsor-name">{sponsor.name}</p>
                <p class="sponsor-tier">Community</p>
              </>
            )}
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section cta-band">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Join Finland’s APIOps Community</h2>
      <p>Advance your API strategy and practices in a focused, collaborative setting.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
        <a class="button primary" href={ticketUrl}>Get Your Ticket</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href={partnerUrl}>View Partnerships</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="footer">
    <div class="container footer-grid">
      <div>
        <h4>APIOps Helsinki 2026</h4>
        <p>Epicenter Helsinki · June 2-3, 2026</p>
        <p>Organized by Osaango in partnership with APIdays.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>Conference</h4>
        <a href="#agenda">Agenda</a>
        <a href="#speakers">Speakers</a>
        <a href="#partners">Partners</a>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>Community</h4>
        <a href="#community">Who Should Attend</a>
        <a href={partnerUrl}>Become a Partner</a>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>Tickets</h4>
        <a href={ticketUrl}>Get your ticket here</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
